olive oil
1 carrot
1 courgette
1 beetroot
½ lemon
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Herb & Mushroom Seasoning
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
½ packet Apricot Sauce
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet garlic aioli
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot and courgette into bite-sized chunks.
Cut beetroot into 1cm chunks.
• Place veggies and Aussie spice blend on a lined
oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with
salt and toss to coat. Roast until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• While the veggies are roasting, slice lemon into
wedges.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince,
mushroom & herb seasoning, fine
breadcrumbs, the egg and a pinch of salt and
pepper.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of
beef mixture into small meatballs (3-4 per
person), then flatten to make 2cm-thick rissoles.
Transfer to a plate.

Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the
ingredients and shaping the mixture into rissoles!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Cook beef rissoles in
batches, until browned and cooked through,
3-4 minutes each side.
• Remove from heat and return all rissoles to
the pan. Add apricot sauce (see ingredients), a
squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of water,
then toss to combine.

• When the veggies are done, add baby spinach
leaves and a squeeze of lemon juice to the oven
tray and toss to combine.

• Divide spiced veggie toss and herby beef rissoles
between plates.
• Serve with garlic aioli and any remaining lemon
wedges. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by drizzling
over the garlic dip!